    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pearson has resided for several years in this village, until recently as the Schoolmaster of the National School—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> During the whole of this time I have never heard even a rumour that he is not quite Trustworthy. As I know nothing of the Duties of an agent for an A. Co<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I cannot pretend to say whether he is very fitted to fulfill them.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established from the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9361.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from A. P. Fletcher, 14 March 1874</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6504.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Pearson</ref> had been appointed schoolmaster of the national school in Down in 1867.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Pearson had applied to be an agent for the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3559.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Northern Assurance Co</ref>mpany. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9361.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from A. P. Fletcher, 14 March 1874</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
